One of the most common beginner compile hitches is a linker error (LNK2019: unresolved external symbol), indicating a function was declared in a header but the compiler could not find its compiled implementation object:

```cpp
// header.h
void PrintPlayerStats(); // Declared

// main.cpp
#include

int main() {
    PrintPlayerStats(); // LNK2019: Linker can't find compiled object for PrintPlayerStats!
    return 0;
}
```
